# RapidAid Admin Dashboard UI Design

## Purpose

The Admin Dashboard provides a centralized interface for system administrators to manage users, hospitals, ambulances, emergency requests, analytics, and system settings.

## Page Layout

### Header

- 🚑 RapidAid Logo
- Dashboard
- Users
- Hospitals
- Ambulances
- Reports
- Settings
- Logout

---

## Dashboard Overview

Display:

- Total Registered Users
- Active Emergency Cases
- Available Ambulances
- Registered Hospitals
- Today's Emergency Requests
- System Health Status

---

## User Management

Display:

- User ID
- Name
- Email
- Mobile Number
- Role
- Account Status

Actions:

- View User
- Edit User
- Suspend User
- Delete User

---

## Hospital Management

Display:

- Hospital Name
- Hospital ID
- Available ICU Beds
- Doctors Available
- Current Status

Actions:

- Add Hospital
- Edit Hospital
- Remove Hospital
- View Details

---

## Ambulance Management

Display:

- Ambulance Number
- Driver Name
- Current Status
- Current Location

Actions:

- Add Ambulance
- Update Details
- Assign Driver
- Remove Ambulance

---

## Emergency Monitoring

Display:

- Emergency ID
- Patient
- Ambulance
- Assigned Hospital
- Status
- Response Time

Actions:

- View Details
- Close Emergency
- Escalate Case

---

## Reports

Generate:

- Daily Reports
- Weekly Reports
- Monthly Reports
- Yearly Reports

Export Formats:

- PDF
- Excel
- CSV

---

## Notifications

Examples:

- New User Registered
- Emergency Escalated
- Hospital Resource Updated
- Ambulance Offline

---

## System Settings

Manage:

- User Roles
- Notification Settings
- API Keys
- Backup & Restore
- Security Settings

---

